         <div type="commentary" subtype="linebyline">
            <list>
               <item corresp="#lb18" xml:space="preserve"><ref>17</ref> <p>The text of the latter part of the line is discussed in Daniel, <emph rend="italics">Architectural Orientation</emph> 69 n. 144, who concludes: "It is likely ... that the writer intended not τόπῳ τῶν ἀρχαγγέλων but rather τόπῳ τὸν ἀρχάγγελον, accusative for genitive (r. τοῦ ἀρχαγγέλλου), and that this was followed by Μιχαήλ, Μιχαηλ[ίο]υ̣ or Μιχαηλ[εί]ο̣υ̣".</p></item>
            </list>
         </div>
